opic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Altman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sarah Friar</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/25/multimedia/25biz-openai-ipo-sam-flvk/25biz-openai-ipo-sam-flvk-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Haiyun Jiang/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Sam Altman, the chief executive of OpenAI, has pushed for a trillion-dollar I.P.O.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>‘The Daily’ and ‘The Opinions’: How A.I. Is Changing Loneliness and Taste</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/podcasts/the-daily-and-the-opinions-how-ai-is-changing-loneliness-and-taste.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/podcasts/the-daily-and-the-opinions-how-ai-is-changing-loneliness-and-taste.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/podcasts/the-daily-and-the-opinions-how-ai-is-changing-loneliness-and-taste.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The story of a woman who let a robot into her home. Plus, a discussion about why Silicon Valley has taken such an interest in taste.</description><dc:creator>Rachel Abrams, Nadja Spiegelman, Olivia Natt, Alex Stern, Asthaa Chaturvedi, Vishakha Darbha, Marc Georges, Chris Haxel, Alyssa Moxley, Carole Sabouraud, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Marion Lozano, Pat McCusker, Diane Wong, Isaac Jones and Aman Sahota</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 11:00:07 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">science</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Robot</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Loneliness</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-audio</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/28/multimedia/28Daily-AI-gtwj/28Daily-AI-gtwj-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Ruth Fremson/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Jan Worrell and her ElliQ. Washington State’s health department provided it to her as part of a pilot program.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Many Child Safety Features on Social Apps Don’t Work, Report Finds</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/29/us/social-media-child-safety-report.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/29/us/social-media-child-safety-report.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/29/us/social-media-child-safety-report.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Researchers found that teens can discover harmful content, connect with unknown adults and easily bypass time limits.</description><dc:creator>Jennifer Valentino-DeVries</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 13:00:06 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Research</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Teens</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Youth</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespa